==Dutch==

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|Nl-worden.ogg|audio|lang=nl}}
* {{IPA|/ˈʋɔr.də(n)/|lang=nl}}

===Etymology===
{{PIE root|nl|wert}}
From {{inh|nl|dum|werden}}, from {{inh|nl|odt|werthan}}, from {{inh|nl|gem-pro|*werþaną}}. Compare German {{m|de|werden}}, Swedish {{m|sv|varda}}, obsolete English {{m|en|worth||to become}} and Latin {{m|la|vertere||turn}}.

===Verb===
{{nl-verb}}

# {{lb|nl|copulative}} to [[become]]
#: {{ux|nl|Zij wilde altijd al lerares '''worden'''.|She always wanted to become a teacher.|inline=1}}
# {{lb|nl|transitive|auxiliary}} Used to form the [[imperfect tense]] of the [[passive voice]], together with a [[past participle]].
#: {{ux|nl|Ze '''worden''' gered.|They are being saved.|inline=1}}
#: {{ux|nl|De muur '''werd''' geschilderd.|The wall was being painted.|inline=1}}
#: {{ux|nl|De muur zal '''worden''' geschilderd.|The wall will be painted. / The wall is going to be painted.|inline=1}}

====Usage notes====
* The [[perfect tense]] passive is formed using [[zijn]].

====Inflection====
{{nl-conj-st|word|werd|worden|aux=zijn}}

